Hata was <EVENT eid="e9" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">replying</EVENT> after an opposition lawmaker <EVENT eid="e10" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">asked</EVENT> if Japan would <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">assist</EVENT>  any US military <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">action</EVENT> in the Korean nuclear <EVENT eid="e13" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">crisis</EVENT>, in addition to <EVENT eid="e14" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">helping</EVENT>  <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">impose</EVENT> any UN <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">sanctions</EVENT> against the hardline communist state.&#13;
Japan's pacifist post-World War II constitution <EVENT eid="e17" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">bars</EVENT> the <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">use</EVENT> of force in  <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">settling</EVENT> international <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">disputes</EVENT>, effectively preventing Japanese troops from  <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">joining</EVENT> UN peace-keeping combat missions.&#13;
But members of Hata's three-week-old cabinet have <EVENT eid="e22" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">suggested</EVENT> new  legislation to <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">expand</EVENT> Japan's emergency activities, including logistical  support for US forces in actions such as a naval blockade.&#13;
